01:24:04.218 --> 01:24:07.278
- Li'l Z', man.
- He's Li'l Z'.


934
01:24:07.888 --> 01:24:10.755
Call that motherfucker!

935
01:24:15.429 --> 01:24:18.296
Go on, man.

936
01:24:18.832 --> 01:24:21.096
Calm down, l'll call him.

937
01:24:54.702 --> 01:24:58.103
My arm! I hurt my arm.
Carrot will have to wait.


938
01:24:58.305 --> 01:25:00.637
That loser got what he deserved.

939
01:25:00.841 --> 01:25:02.832
Let's go!

940
01:25:26.567 --> 01:25:30.503
Gerson...

941
01:25:30.704 --> 01:25:34.299
That bastard killed my brother.

942
01:25:42.249 --> 01:25:45.013
I can't let that go.

943
01:26:00.234 --> 01:26:02.361
- Want a gun?
- My son...


944
01:26:02.569 --> 01:26:05.970
Calm down, mom.

945
01:26:06.807 --> 01:26:09.674
Please, mom...

946
01:26:18.485 --> 01:26:22.148
Do it right, asshole.

947
01:26:22.356 --> 01:26:26.087
- There's no other way.
- How'd I let that loser hit me?


948
01:26:26.293 --> 01:26:28.761
Shit, that's some hole.

949
01:26:58.492 --> 01:27:01.484
- It's as if we were brothers.
- Shut up.


950
01:27:01.695 --> 01:27:06.223
Both of us hurt in the arm.
You by one brother, me the other.


951
01:27:06.433 --> 01:27:10.233
It would be really funny
if we were brothers.


952
01:27:10.437 --> 01:27:16.535
That Knockout Ned's not bad, eh?
He came out of nowhere.


953
01:27:17.311 --> 01:27:20.940
Shut up, Tuba!
You're a fucking pain!


954
01:27:28.489 --> 01:27:32.653
It was as if the City of God
had suddenly found a hero.


955
01:27:32.860 --> 01:27:35.021
God bless you, son.

956
01:27:35.229 --> 01:27:38.494
That kid was just asking
to be killed.


957
01:27:38.699 --> 01:27:41.395
Well done.

958
01:27:41.602 --> 01:27:44.833
You did a good job.

959
01:27:45.038 --> 01:27:48.667
You'd better go hide.

960
01:27:51.278 --> 01:27:54.543
I thought Knockout Ned
would start a revolution here.


961
01:27:54.748 --> 01:27:57.512
But God had other plans.

962
01:27:57.818 --> 01:28:01.413
Steak,
where are all the dealers?


963
01:28:01.622 --> 01:28:04.887
They're hiding.
Li'l Z' is in a bad mood.


964
01:28:05.092 --> 01:28:08.823
They get us hooked and then
they go off and hide.


965
01:28:09.029 --> 01:28:12.260
Do me a favor. Go get some
nose candy for me.


966
01:28:12.466 --> 01:28:13.865
I'll try.

967
01:28:14.067 --> 01:28:17.525
Tell them it's for Thiago,
to keep my buzz going.


968
01:28:38.124 --> 01:28:43.494
Steak'n'fries,
go to Carrot's and tell him...


969
01:28:43.696 --> 01:28:49.066
Li'l Z' says that if you kill
Knockout, he'll leave you alone.


970
01:28:49.702 --> 01:28:52.569
Hey, Knockout Ned.
Did you hear that?


971
01:28:52.772 --> 01:28:55.434
Grab the kid!

972
01:28:57.610 --> 01:29:03.276
You heard the boy? If you don't
stick with us, you're dead.


973
01:29:03.483 --> 01:29:06.748
I think you should join us.
We'll be partners.


974
01:29:07.420 --> 01:29:10.355
Drugs aren't my thing.

975
01:29:10.557 --> 01:29:12.684
This is just something
between me and him.


976
01:29:12.892 --> 01:29:17.556
Those guys aren't worth shit.

977
01:29:17.764 --> 01:29:21.359
They'll do anything for power.

978
01:29:21.568 --> 01:29:23.900
Like that kid.

979
01:29:24.103 --> 01:29:28.233
They're all robots,
like this punk here.


980
01:29:28.441 --> 01:29:30.705
What's in your head, kid?

981
01:29:30.910 --> 01:29:33.344
Can't you see you're
wrecking your life...


982
01:29:33.546 --> 01:29:37.778
with that maniac and a bunch
of trigger-happy fools?


983
01:29:39.252 --> 01:29:45.919
- Are you crazy? You're just a kid.
- A kid? I smoke, snort...


984
01:29:46.125 --> 01:29:49.424
l've killed and robbed.
I'm a man.


985
01:29:49.629 --> 01:29:52.154
Shit, you have no idea!

986
01:29:52.365 --> 01:29:55.596
He's attached to his gang.
You should join up with us.


987
01:29:55.802 --> 01:30:00.671
- Shall we kill him?
- Steak, we're going to grind you.


988
01:30:02.275 --> 01:30:06.507
- Okay, I accept.
- Great!


989
01:30:06.713 --> 01:30:10.809
Tell your boss that Knockout Ned
and Carrot are now in command.


990
01:30:11.017 --> 01:30:17.217
But on one condition:
No killing of innocent people.


991
01:30:18.858 --> 01:30:21.452
I can't accept that, understand?

992
01:30:21.661 --> 01:30:26.325
Okay, no innocent people.

993
01:30:27.734 --> 01:30:32.671
Steak fucked up!

994
01:30:44.350 --> 01:30:46.944
- Have you a gun for me?
- No...


995
01:30:47.153 --> 01:30:50.554
but we can hold up
a gun store.


996
01:30:50.757 --> 01:30:52.816
That's no problem.

997
01:30:53.026 --> 01:30:56.621
I don't want to hold up anything.
I'm not a hoodlum.


998
01:30:56.829 --> 01:31:00.026
This is a personal affair
between me and him, okay?


999
01:31:00.700 --> 01:31:02.964
I'm not a hoodlum.

1000
01:31:05.338 --> 01:31:07.306
He raped your chick...

1001
01:31:07.507 --> 01:31:11.341
killed your uncle and brother,
gunned your house...


1002
01:31:11.544 --> 01:31:14.911
and you killed one of his guys.

1003
01:31:19.251 --> 01:31:22.880
If you're not a hood,
then get out.


1004
01:31:27.960 --> 01:31:32.397
THE STORY OF KNOCKOUT NED

1005
01:31:33.565 --> 01:31:36.056
This is a hold-up!

1006
01:31:44.109 --> 01:31:47.738
- The first time...
- Where are the revolvers?


1007
01:31:47.946 --> 01:31:51.575
...Knockout Ned saved a salesclerk
from being shot by Carrot.


1008
01:31:51.783 --> 01:31:56.186
We said no killing!

1009
01:31:56.388 --> 01:31:58.185
That's the rule.

1010
01:31:59.424 --> 01:32:04.657
We want the boss' money. Everyone
keep calm. Open the cash register!


1011
01:32:04.863 --> 01:32:07.764
You want us to go?
We do too.


1012
01:32:07.966 --> 01:32:10.400
So hurry up!

1013
01:32:11.637 --> 01:32:14.037
- Look at the ground!
- The second time...


1014
01:32:14.239 --> 01:32:16.173
Carrot saved
Knockout Ned's life.


1015
01:32:18.944 --> 01:32:22.072
Ned learned that there's
an exception to every rule.


1016
01:32:22.714 --> 01:32:25.046
Exception to the rule.

1017
01:32:25.250 --> 01:32:28.344
- Are you the manager?
- Yes.


1018
01:32:28.553 --> 01:32:32.546
This is a hold-up.
Everyone on the ground!


1019
01:32:32.758 --> 01:32:34.783
On the ground!

1020
01:32:34.993 --> 01:32:39.225
Give me the money!

1021
01:32:42.167 --> 01:32:44.397
I'm not kidding.

1022
01:32:44.603 --> 01:32:46.833
The first person who moves
is dead!


1023
01:32:47.239 --> 01:32:50.868
The third time, the exception
becomes the rule.


1024
01:33:06.658 --> 01:33:11.027
Carrot and Knockout Ned
prepared to face Li'l Z'.


1025
01:33:11.229 --> 01:33:14.027
Carrot could protect his
business.


1026
01:33:14.299 --> 01:33:16.062
Knockout Ned...

1027
01:33:16.268 --> 01:33:19.203
the best marksman in his battalion,
wanted revenge.


1028
01:33:19.404 --> 01:33:23.602
First, the Italians.
This is a 9 mm.


1029
01:33:24.343 --> 01:33:26.573
- Let me see.
- Not bad, eh?


1030
01:33:26.778 --> 01:33:31.477
- The sight isn't well-aligned.
- I'll give you a good price.


1031
01:33:32.284 --> 01:33:34.275
The 12 mm, the "hand job".

1032
01:33:34.920 --> 01:33:36.148
See why?

1033
01:33:36.355 --> 01:33:39.415
An Uzi, 9 mm. It's Israeli.

1034
01:33:39.624 --> 01:33:42.491
- The star of David.
- Jewish.


1035
01:33:42.694 --> 01:33:44.059
I want a 30-06.

1036
01:33:44.529 --> 01:33:46.895
Now we can start having fun.

1037
01:33:47.099 --> 01:33:51.433
The war's on.
Let's start with a prayer.


1038
01:33:51.803 --> 01:33:55.899
Our Father who art in heaven
hallowed be our name...


1039
01:33:56.108 --> 01:34:00.272
Our will be done...

1040
01:34:00.812 --> 01:34:03.303
On earth as it is in heaven...

1041
01:34:16.561 --> 01:34:18.620
Hoodlums have guns,
but can't shoot.


1042
01:34:18.930 --> 01:34:22.957
One bullet from Knockout Ned
was worth ten from Li'l Zs gang.


1043
01:34:23.168 --> 01:34:27.298
Li'l Z' couldn't take it.
He counter-attacked.


1044
01:34:29.941 --> 01:34:34.173
The ghetto had been a purgatory,
now it was hell.


1045
01:34:38.116 --> 01:34:43.816
I decided to get out.
That's how I became a reporter.


1046
01:34:44.689 --> 01:34:47.123
Great photo!

1047
01:34:47.325 --> 01:34:49.793
I bet it's by Rogerio Reis.

1048
01:34:50.362 --> 01:34:53.195
What did I tell you?

1049
01:34:53.398 --> 01:34:55.593
Like any pro...

1050
01:34:55.801 --> 01:34:59.237
I started at the bottom,
way down at the bottom.


1051
01:34:59.438 --> 01:35:02.896
Without knowing what awaited me.

1052
01:35:04.543 --> 01:35:07.512
Instead of going home
l'd go over to the paper.


1053
01:35:07.712 --> 01:35:11.079
A guy from the City of God
worked in the lab.


1054
01:35:11.283 --> 01:35:14.150
Check this out.

1055
01:35:14.352 --> 01:35:18.413
He helped me move closer to
what I loved most in life.


1056
01:35:18.623 --> 01:35:20.250
- Hi, Rogerio.
- How are you, Pierre?


1057
01:35:20.459 --> 01:35:23.087
This is Rocket.
He's a photographer.


1058
01:35:23.295 --> 01:35:24.455
Hello, Rocket.

1059
01:35:24.663 --> 01:35:26.927
- He's a fan of yours.
- Really?


1060
01:35:27.132 --> 01:35:28.759
You have good taste, Rocket!

1061
01:35:28.967 --> 01:35:32.061
- Well, l'm done. I'm off.
- See you.


1062
01:35:32.270 --> 01:35:34.932
What a cool guy!

1063
01:35:35.740 --> 01:35:38.834
What should have been
a swift revenge...


1064
01:35:39.044 --> 01:35:41.535
turned into an all-out war.

1065
01:35:46.651 --> 01:35:48.881
The City of God was divided.

1066
01:35:49.087 --> 01:35:52.887
You couldn't go from one
section to the other.


1067
01:35:53.091 --> 01:35:55.321
Not even to visit a relative.

1068
01:35:55.527 --> 01:35:59.258
The cops considered anyone
living in the ghetto a hoodlum.


1069
01:35:59.464 --> 01:36:02.900
People got used to living
in Vietnam.


1070
01:36:07.105 --> 01:36:12.065
And more and more volunteers
kept signing up to die.


1071
01:36:12.277 --> 01:36:13.266
This kid...

1072
01:36:13.478 --> 01:36:16.208
- What do you want?
- A boy from Carrot's gang punched me.


1073
01:36:16.748 --> 01:36:18.113
The war was
an excuse for everything.


1074
01:36:18.517 --> 01:36:20.485
One of Li'l Zs soldiers
kicked me.


1075
01:36:22.521 --> 01:36:24.546
Take this.22.

1076
01:36:26.358 --> 01:36:28.826
The jerk who raped my sister is
with Carrot.


1077
01:36:29.027 --> 01:36:30.426
Li'l Z' evicted my family.

1078
01:36:31.463 --> 01:36:33.090
Kill... Be respected.

1079
01:36:45.477 --> 01:36:50.938
- I'm Thiago, a friend of Benny's.
- Can you read? Can you add?


1080
01:36:51.149 --> 01:36:56.587
- I'm pretty good in business.
- Okay, get to work.


1081
01:36:57.088 --> 01:37:00.455
- What do you want?
- To get my father's murderer.


1082
01:37:00.859 --> 01:37:03.623
- What's your name?
- My name's Otto.


1083
01:37:09.067 --> 01:37:11.035
What's the matter?

1084
01:37:11.236 --> 01:37:15.195
- He's a worker.
- But he wants a gun.


1085
01:37:15.941 --> 01:37:18.603
He won't last a week.

1086
01:37:29.621 --> 01:37:34.456
A year later, no one
remembered how it had all begun.


1087
01:37:34.659 --> 01:37:35.990
Take that!

1088
01:37:38.797 --> 01:37:44.736
For both sides, the aim was to take
over the enemy's business in order...


1089
01:37:44.936 --> 01:37:48.463
to buy more guns and take over
more businesses.


1090
01:38:10.295 --> 01:38:13.492
I smoke, snort,
l've killed and robbed.


1091
01:38:13.698 --> 01:38:16.030
I'm a man.

1092
01:38:37.689 --> 01:38:42.717
The media started taking an interest.
The police had to intervene.


1093
01:38:56.675 --> 01:39:01.078
A gang leader, from the City of God,
was arrested today.


1094
01:39:01.279 --> 01:39:03.008
Manuel Machado,
a.k.a. Knockout Ned...


1095
01:39:03.214 --> 01:39:06.615
was hospitalized after being
wounded by Li'l Zs gang.


1096
01:39:06.818 --> 01:39:09.048
Our reporter interviewed him.

1097
01:39:09.254 --> 01:39:13.213
- Is the war still going on?
- It's still going on.


1098
01:39:13.491 --> 01:39:18.019
- Have many people died?
- Many have died.


1099
01:39:18.229 --> 01:39:20.356
Mostly innocent people.

1100
01:39:20.565 --> 01:39:23.932
Just knowing me is enough...

1101
01:39:24.135 --> 01:39:28.868
to get you killed by Li'l Z'.

1102
01:39:29.074 --> 01:39:32.441
- The police don't go in there?
- They go after me, not him.


1103
01:39:32.644 --> 01:39:38.981
I've been in jail, while he goes
on killing undisturbed.


1104
01:39:39.184 --> 01:39:41.277
And they don't arrest him.

1105
01:39:41.486 --> 01:39:43.784
Knockout Ned says
the war will continue.


1106
01:39:43.988 --> 01:39:49.585
Police Chief Guedes has promised
to arrest both of the gangs.


1107
01:39:58.069 --> 01:39:59.798
Motherfucker!

1108
01:40:00.004 --> 01:40:03.565
I'm the boss here, but he gets
his picture in the paper!


1109
01:40:03.775 --> 01:40:07.336
- Have you found mine?
- Just Knockout Ned's.


1110
01:40:07.545 --> 01:40:09.012
Keep looking.

1111
01:40:09.414 --> 01:40:12.144
At least my name's
got to be in there.


1112
01:40:12.350 --> 01:40:14.045
- There's nothing.
- Can you read?


1113
01:40:14.252 --> 01:40:16.686
Just the pictures.

1114
01:40:17.655 --> 01:40:19.714
Nothing.

1115
01:40:19.924 --> 01:40:23.018
Hey, what the fuck are you doing?

1116
01:40:23.228 --> 01:40:28.359
- It's just the want ads.
- I don't care, read everything!


1117
01:40:28.566 --> 01:40:32.730
- But there aren't any articles.
- Want a bullet in your head?


1118
01:40:34.739 --> 01:40:38.231
Gotta show them who's boss here.

1119
01:40:43.281 --> 01:40:46.978
- Give me the camera!
- No way!


1120
01:40:49.521 --> 01:40:51.853
Take my picture, man.

1121
01:40:52.457 --> 01:40:55.187
I can't work it.

1122
01:40:55.393 --> 01:40:57.088
Go ahead.

1123
01:40:57.462 --> 01:41:02.024
- I'll hold the Beretta.
- Let me try...


1124
01:41:02.667 --> 01:41:05.363
Back off...

1125
01:41:05.570 --> 01:41:09.836
- There's no click.
- What a bunch of bozos!


1126
01:41:10.341 --> 01:41:13.105
I'm fucked with you guys.

1127
01:41:15.180 --> 01:41:17.740
I have an idea.

1128
01:41:17.949 --> 01:41:22.477
I'll go get a guy I know.
Hang loose.


1129
01:41:23.354 --> 01:41:27.256
- Here he is.
- Take the camera.


1130
01:41:27.959 --> 01:41:30.393
Well, kid?

1131
01:41:31.462 --> 01:41:36.866
Aren't you a photographer?
Make the camerawork. We can't do it.


1132
01:41:38.670 --> 01:41:40.467
Take our picture.

1133
01:41:45.410 --> 01:41:49.210
- You fucking broke it.
- It wasn't me.


1134
01:41:49.781 --> 01:41:51.476
I found it.

1135
01:41:53.318 --> 01:41:55.479
It has to be wound.

1136
01:41:59.924 --> 01:42:02.916
- What's your name?
- Rocket.


1137
01:42:03.294 --> 01:42:07.230
- Another picture, Rocket.
- How about two rows?


1138
01:42:07.432 --> 01:42:12.335
- What?
- Two rows. Everyone with their guns.


1139
01:42:13.104 --> 01:42:17.131
- You're outside, for Christ's sake!
- Talk to him nicely, kid.


1140
01:42:17.342 --> 01:42:19.276
Sorry. Move in, please.

1141
01:42:21.779 --> 01:42:24.247
Another one.

1142
01:42:28.620 --> 01:42:30.918
- I think the roll's finished.
- Then show us the pictures.


1143
01:42:31.122 --> 01:42:33.989
- They have to be developed.
- Developed?


1144
01:42:35.226 --> 01:42:36.887
How much is it?

1145
01:42:37.495 --> 01:42:41.898
Take this money.
And bring back the pictures.


1146
01:42:42.100 --> 01:42:47.367
- I have to remove the film.
- Keep the camera.


1147
01:42:47.872 --> 01:42:52.275
Benny wanted to give it to you,
didn't he? So, it's yours...


1148
01:42:52.477 --> 01:42:54.308
Thanks.

1149
01:42:56.247 --> 01:43:00.445
Don't forget the pictures.
The photos, Rocket!


1150
01:43:11.529 --> 01:43:13.861
- Pierre!
- What?


1151
01:43:14.265 --> 01:43:17.632
Can you develop this for me?

1152
01:43:18.336 --> 01:43:21.794
I can't, Rocket.
I could get into trouble.


1153
01:43:22.006 --> 01:43:24.736
It's only for the paper's reporters.
I could risk my job.


1154
01:43:24.943 --> 01:43:26.433
- Pierre?
- Yes, Rogerio?


1155
01:43:26.644 --> 01:43:31.274
Develop these for me.
This one too, okay?


1156
01:43:31.683 --> 01:43:34.049
I'm going to lunch.

1157
01:43:34.252 --> 01:43:38.348
You're lucky. What size?

1158
01:43:38.556 --> 01:43:41.957
- What?
- For the enlargement, what size?


1159
01:43:42.427 --> 01:43:46.227
Well... Whatever you think is best.

1160
01:44:06.017 --> 01:44:08.144
- Here.
- Thanks.


1161
01:44:12.023 --> 01:44:14.685
I'm in deep shit now.

1162
01:44:16.594 --> 01:44:19.119
I'm as good as dead.

1163
01:44:30.375 --> 01:44:32.468
Someone had signed
my death sentence.


1164
01:44:32.677 --> 01:44:36.135
I wanted to bash the jerk's face in.

1165
01:44:41.819 --> 01:44:45.448
Are you Marina?
Because of you l'm dead.


1166
01:44:45.656 --> 01:44:47.783
You stole my photos.

1167
01:44:47.992 --> 01:44:51.860
Dead? Stole? What do you mean?
Not so loud.


1168
01:44:53.164 --> 01:44:55.689
Not so loud?
I'll be killed because of you.


1169
01:44:55.900 --> 01:44:58.460
You were gone,
